msg: On the pin-externals branch, while pinning externals use the correct
path for externals which were moved since the last-changed revision.
the path an external had at its last-changed revision. Use the obtained
path when pinning to the last changed revision in case the path differs
from external's path in the youngest revision.
An unfortunate side-effect is that relative externals may become absolute
when pinning, because I could not come up with a reliable way of
transforming a resolved absolute URL into relative external URL syntax.
